2. Find the column index of the header “last 4 trend”.
3. For each player row, gather the scores from the date columns (2‑15), filter out None, take the last four values, compute their arithmetic mean (if fewer than four, average whatever is present; if none, leave blank).
4. Write the result (rounded to two decimals) into the target cell.
5. Save the workbook to the output directory with the same filename.
6. Call `recalculate` to evaluate any remaining formulas.
7. Reload the file (data_only) and verify that the “last 4 trend” column now contains numeric values for each player.
